ef9.textContent:
Synthesis pathways for biogenic amines
follow solid arrows through enzymatic steps,
while degradation steps follow dashed arrows.

pathway.author: [MaintBot, Thomas, Christine Chichester, Mkutmon, Eweitz]

comments.content: This pathway was inferred from Homo sapiens pathway [http://www.wikipathways.org/index.php?title=Pathway:WP550&amp;amp;amp;oldid=21838 WP550(r21838)] with a 50% conversion rate.

Biogenic amines are one of two broad classes of classical neurotransmitters (the other being amino acids) and include: acetylcholine, serotonin, histamine, and the catecholamines epinephrine, norepinephrine, and dopamine. 

Source: http://www.whatislife.com/reader2/Metabolism/pathway/Neurotransmitter.html
